x4codes.hlp: Univ. of Toronto, Toronto, Ontario, Canada

x4freetext: was used for the energy range 270-1100
keV with beam current of up 160 Mu-A. Beam energy
spread <1 keV, error of energy calibration <2 keV.
Supplied a proton beam of up 40 Mu-A in
the energy range 800-3600 keV.  Error of energy
calibration 0.04% and energy spread <3 keV.
For one set of experiments at the 350 keV accelerator
Ti-N solid targets were used.  The targets, 10 keV,
approximately, thick at 280 keV, were produced by
evaporating a thin layer of Ti onto a thick Ta backing
and nitriding the Ti layer in a nitrogen atmosphere by
resistance heating.
In the experiments at the 350 keV accelerator
windowless gas target systems of the extended type or
of the quasi-point supersonic Jet Type were used too.
At the energy >0.4 MeV 14-N ions were implanted in
0.1 mm thick Ta sheets.
Of some levels of O-15.

x4freetext: - By Authors - The cross section of direct capture to
6.79-MeV state was determined as 580 +/- 85 nb
in Rel-Ref. U.Schroeder gives 720 +/- 140 nb  in
his thesis. The value in Data Section is weighted
average of both measurements.
